    <mxCell id="params" value="&lt;b&gt;Unstable steady state&lt;/b&gt; (Table 3)&#10;A&lt;sub&gt;f,s&lt;/sub&gt; = 0.500 mol/ft&#179;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;A&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt; = 0.245 mol/ft&#179;&#10;T&lt;sub&gt;f,s&lt;/sub&gt; = 530 &#176;R&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;T&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt; = 600 &#176;R&#10;T&lt;sub&gt;c,f,s&lt;/sub&gt; = 530 &#176;R&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;T&lt;sub&gt;c,s&lt;/sub&gt; = 541 &#176;R&#10;q&lt;sub&gt;s&lt;/sub&gt;/V = 0.833 h&#8315;&#185;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;q&lt;sub&gt;c,s&lt;/sub&gt;/V&lt;sub&gt;J&lt;/sub&gt; = 13.0 h&#8315;&#185;&#10;k&#8320; = 7.08&#215;10&#185;&#8304; h&#8315;&#185;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;E&#8336;/R = 15 100 &#176;R" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333333;strokeColor=#cccccc;fillColor=#f7f7f7;spacing=8;" vertex="1" parent="1">
      <mxGeometry x="700" y="360" width="420" height="128" as="geometry"/>
    </mxCell>

    <mxCell id="eqn" value="(&#8722;&#916;H)/&#961;C&lt;sub&gt;p&lt;/sub&gt; = 800 &#176;R&#183;ft&#179;/mol&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;U&#8320;S/(V&#961;C&lt;sub&gt;p&lt;/sub&gt;) = 1.90 h&#8315;&#185;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;U&#8320;S/(V&lt;sub&gt;J&lt;/sub&gt;&#961;&lt;sub&gt;c&lt;/sub&gt;C&lt;sub&gt;p,c&lt;/sub&gt;) = 2.48 h&#8315;&#185;&#10;Three states: A, T, T&lt;sub&gt;c&lt;/sub&gt;. Because the jacket is perfectly mixed, the coolant leaves &lt;b&gt;at the jacket temperature T&lt;sub&gt;c&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &#8212; there is no separate outlet temperature." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#333333;strokeColor=#cccccc;fillColor=#f7f7f7;spacing=8;" vertex="1" parent="1">
      <mxGeometry x="100" y="660" width="1020" height="60" as="geometry"/>
    </mxCell>

    <mxCell id="caveat" value="The paper contains no process schematic; this diagram is composed from its equations and Table 3. Heat-transfer area S and coefficient U&#8320; are given only as the grouped ratios above, never individually.&#10;&lt;b&gt;The paper does not state which end of the jacket the coolant enters&lt;/b&gt; &#8212; bottom-in / top-out is drawn by convention, not from the source. The coolant control valve, two thermocouples and composition analyzer specified in the paper belong to the control layer and are omitted here." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=10;fontColor=#777777;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;spacing=4;" vertex="1" parent="1">
      <mxGeometry x="100" y="728" width="1020" height="60" as="geometry"/>
